Pretoria - Time Square and the Pretoria News once again joined hands with Rise Against Hunger to pack meals for hungry children in underprivileged communities. The food packing drive is part of a nationwide effort between Sun International and Rise Against Hunger to mark International Mandela Day. Teams of volunteers rolled-up their sleeves to pack food parcels at eight Sun International venues. The goal is to pack 418 000 meals to feed over 59 000 pre-school children for a year. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
